name: Interstate transfer fee
text: §353B-6  Interstate transfer fee.  The judiciary may assess a fee not to exceed $200 for each application made by a parolee or probationer for a transfer out of the State; provided that the fees collected shall be deposited into the probation services special fund established in section 706-649. [L 2008, c 172, §1; am L 2012, c 303, §1]
